answer.p:
The answers from the prior subsection show the row operations. Each answer here just lists the solution set, the particular solution, and the homogeneous solution.


The solution set is
						\bigl\{\vec{\frac{2}{3} -\frac{1}{3} 0} + \vec{\frac{1}{6}  \frac{2}{3}  1}z \mid z \text{ in  } \R\bigr\}
					A particular solution and the solution set for the associated homogeneous system are here.
						\vec{\frac{2}{3}  -\frac{1}{3} 0} \qquad \bigl\{\vec{\frac{1}{6} \frac{2}{3}  1}z \mid z \text{ in } \R\bigr\}


The solution set is infinite:
						\bigl\{\vec{1  3 0  0} + \vec{1 -2  1  0}z \mid z \text{ in }\R\bigr\}
						Here are a particular solution and the solution set for the associated homogeneous system.
						\vec{1  3  0  0} \qquad \bigl\{\vec{1  -2  1 0}z \mid z\text{ in  }\R\bigr\}


This is the solution set.
						 \bigl\{\vec{0  0  0  0} + \vec{-1  0 1 0}z + \vec{-1  -1  0  1}w \mid z, w\text{ in }\R\bigr\}
						Here is a particular solution and the solution set for the associated homogeneous system.
						 \vec{0  0  0  0} \qquad \bigl\{\vec{-1  0  1  0}z +\vec{-1  -1  0  1}w \mid z, w \text{ in }\R\bigr\}


The solution set is this.
						\bigl\{\vec{1  0  0  0  0} +\vec{-\frac{5}{7}  -\frac{8}{7}  1  0  0}c +\vec{-\frac{3}{7}  -\frac{2}{7}  0  1  0}d +\vec{-\frac{1}{7}  \frac{4}{7}  0  0  1}e \mid c, d, e\text{ in  }\R\bigr\}
						And, this is a particular solution and the solution set for the associated homogeneous system.
						 \vec{1 0  0  0  0} \qquad \bigl\{\vec{1  0  0  0  0} +\vec{-\frac{5}{7}  -\frac{8}{7}  1  0  0}c +\vec{-\frac{3}{7}  -\frac{2}{7}  0  1  0}d +\vec{-\frac{1}{7}  \frac{4}{7}  0  0  1}e \mid c, d, e\text{ in  }\R\bigr\}

