ol.li:
Row reduction gives


								\amat{1 3 8 0 1; 0 1 2 1 1; 0 1 2 4 1} \longsquiggly[] \amat{1 0 2 0 -2;0 1 2 0 1; 0 0 0 1 0}


						The parametric form of the solution set is

							\vec{x_1 x_2 x_3 x_4} = x_3\vec{-2 -2 1 0} + \vec{-2 1 0 0}

						Solution set as a translate of the span is
						\vec{-2 1 0 0} + \Span\{\vec{-2 -2 1 0}\}.
